### What is AWCP?

The Agent Workspace Collaboration Protocol (AWCP) is a standardized workspace delegation primitive designed for deep-engagement collaboration across remote agents. It addresses the gap in existing frameworks by providing explicit lifecycle management and transport-agnostic file synchronization.

### Current Status

The current status of the AWCP project can be found on GitHub at <https://github.com/SII-Holos/awcp>. The project is active, and several papers and articles have been published discussing its benefits and applications. However, there is limited information available on the current implementation and adoption of AWCP.

### Conclusion

The AWCP project has the potential to revolutionize deep-engagement collaboration across remote agents by providing a standardized workspace delegation protocol. While there is currently limited information available on its current status, further research and development are likely to continue in this area.


